  "body": "Assume I write this\r\n\r\n`this.setState({ctr:1});\r\n`\r\nNow, assume **state hasn't been updated yet** as a result of above call, and I write:\r\n\r\n`this.setState((ps)=>{console.log(ps.ctr)})\r\n`\r\nWill I see value \"1\"?\r\n\r\nBasically question is about if there is a _pending state update_ from a \"_Normal_\" (not functional) setState, will the previousState that I receive in _functional setState,_ capture that pending value?",
